description:
&lt;p&gt;Part Time 18.75 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting oppourtunity has arisen for a Support Secretary within the Respiratory Team in Singleton Hospital. The Support Secretary is responsible for supporting the COPD Early Discharge Service (EDS) and providing an efficient and comprehensive administrative and typing service for the COPD EDS Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Support Secretary will maintain a direct and close working relationship with the COPD EDS Team, as well as Nursing, Therapies, Consultant and Medical staff, other staff within the Department, Medical Secretaries, Medical Support Manager and other support staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to work across both Singleton and Morriston sites to provide support to COPD teams across both sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to manage their own workload and therefore act independently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eve JeffreyAssociate Services Manager&lt;/p&gt;
